Package movement

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Castle
    A type of moveclass which requires you to move to another piece, then put that piece on the other side of the first piece to protect it.
    Move
    A move is a set of relative coordinates, to which a piece may move.
    MoveClass
    A set of moves which are dynamically generated based on the position of the piece and other pieces on the board.
    MoveHistory
    Records the old position and new position of a piece.
    MoveSet
    A MoveSet is a bundle of moves, in any datatype, which can behave in multiple ways.
    Touple
    An immutable set of coordinates on a chess board.
